<subSubSection id="EA7A3425A9712E543FFB207BC2E3AFB7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="22A303F7B2E18A82CAF5C2C18D9FA33A" pageNumber="317">Etymology Named in honor of Louis M. Roth, distinguished insect systematist and friend, who accompanied me on my first field trip to Costa Rica in 1959.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7151C48639721B2A2BFE72422A4DC59A" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2F73E4CA9772B02B7FDBA67CD98224DB" pageNumber="317">
Diagnosis A very large blackish (major) or reddish (minor) brown member of the 
<taxonomicName id="333094AB73681A773B821FB864C81E80" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group, distinguished in the major by its long propodeal spines, largely rugoreticulate dorsal head surface, and almost completely rugulose and carinulate sides of the mesosoma; and in the minor by the rugulose mesopleuron and propodeum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="512D62EBC8ED61B9FD24CF82715CB6EF" type="description">
<paragraph id="F393707A1F8C01AEE7711F153D6CC8F3" pageNumber="317">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BFD95A2878A66014A028D49B70E05E63" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33573" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole ajax Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole ajax Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ajax">ajax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="845339C1BD5AEC4B4AE3185DEAA5C2F1" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33743" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fiorii Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fiorii Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiorii">fiorii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6865F89B56E998F19325ACFB3752217" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole hector Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole hector Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hector">hector</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8B3CA51ED042A4D948EB1C847F2DC12D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33782" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole hirsuta Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole hirsuta Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">hirsuta</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="B15F7ABB48C2D769A9D1D90565A226A0" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181792" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jaculifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jaculifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaculifera">jaculifera</taxonomicName>
, differing in many details of body form, sculpturing, and pilosity, as illustrated. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.88, HL 1.80, SL 1.04, EL 0.30, PW 0.84. Paratype minor: HW 0.78, HL 0.92, SL 1.16, EL 0.22, PW 0.60.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="789A0FE16D5DB6EE036C958CBBF7BF50" pageNumber="317">color Major: body blackish brown, head also with a faint reddish tinge; mandibles dark reddish brown; scape and legs except tarsi medium brown; funiculus and tarsi brownish yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4CB8386715005453F430D4A43780D30D" pageNumber="317">Minor: gaster dark brown, rest of body medium reddish brown; appendages light reddish brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2ECFEEE88A19AA3322E9EFACC321D93E" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D524959B7497BBEEDB61173AB0327EA5" pageNumber="317">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DAE356888BF3E6626F587B6E2BECED53" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="7886442B1A3A134EF4B25D19225227AD" pageNumber="317">Biology The type colony was collected by Philip S. Ward from a rotten log on the floor of rainforest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
